This paper presents a new agent architecture for reinforcement learning, which involves algorithmic and architectural contributions. The paper focuses on improving sample efficiency and run-time performance, which are key concerns in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses Atari 2600 benchmarks, which suggests a possible association with computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
